cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "structural-isomorphism v1.0 cross-domain SOC + universality benchmark"
abstract: >
  A Zenodo-deposited reference benchmark for cross-domain self-organized
  criticality (SOC), preferential attachment, and adjacent universality-class
  validation. The bundle ships 13 independently fetched empirical systems
  (USGS earthquakes, S&P 500 returns, three DeFi liquidation streams, mouse
  ALM cortex avalanches from DANDI:000006, NIFC US wildfires, GOES X-ray
  solar flares 2000-2016, FDIC bank failures 1934-2026, GitHub stargazer
  counts, North-American power-grid cascades, English Wikipedia pageviews,
  a Hawkes-Omori synthetic baseline, Fox River dissolved-oxygen for a
  Scheffer fold-bifurcation reference, and the US-101 NGSIM q-rho hysteresis
  panel) together with four synthetic null controls that the same fitting
  pipeline correctly rejects. The bundle includes the frozen Clauset-MLE +
  bootstrap-CI + b-value + Omori + universal-collapse pipeline as a
  reusable PyPI-style Python package, a 35-class universality-class taxonomy
  with two layers of LLM-critic curation (B1 single-Opus + B3 three-DeepSeek
  ensemble), the full layer-3 critic and layer-4 prediction JSONL outputs,
  a reproduce_all.py one-shot reproducibility entry point, and a tutorial
  notebook reproducing the Phase 1 earthquake b-value in under 30 minutes
  on a laptop.
